Container:
	- application,
	- logging-agent
	- proxy
	we can put all the thing within container but increase the process and hard to manage the sequence and kill one of them when needed
Pod:
	- put one or more container within the pod and run single pod instead a container
	- container within the pod share resources CPU, memory, disk

Kubernetes:
	- container orchestration
	- application, load-balancing, config-registry
	- can manage 1000s of container(micro-services)